sentences: Kyung Soo-jin (born November 5, 1987) is a South Korean actress.
After supporting roles in Man from the Equator, That Winter, the Wind Blows and Shark, she played her first leading role in TV Novel: Eunhui.
In November 2018, Kyung signed with YG Entertainment.
On December 16, 2021, it was reported that Kyung had decided to renew her contract with YG Entertainment.
